.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-CACHE\-PRUNE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.20" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-cache\-prune \- Prune cached image artifacts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose cache prune [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Delete cached artifacts by age or delete artifacts that the current compose plan no longer references.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file whose plan defines the live cache references.
.TP
\fB--cache\-dir\fR \fICACHE_DIR\fR
Cache directory to prune instead of the default or plan cache path.
.TP
\fB--age\fR \fIDAYS\fR
Remove cached artifacts older than this many days.
.TP
\fB--all\-unused\fR
Remove cached artifacts that the current compose plan no longer references.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose cache prune \-\-age 14
hpc\-compose cache prune \-\-all\-unused \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose cache prune \-\-age 7 \-\-format json
.fi
